We are planning to use different colour schemes for different groups confluence spaces. However, that is quite a tedious task to accomplish as there is only one global custom colour scheme possible. Forcing us to manually having to edit for new spaces needing a different scheme.

Much better would be if it was possible, like for so many other features, to create any number of named colour schemes. Then simply select the one to use for a space.

That would both make it much quicker to apply a colour scheme and, when needed, make a change to the scheme and have it applied automatically on all spaces using it.

