It is very annoying, really! I have tried to get links to work all day, but whatever I do, when I save an edited page, the link that I just entered and validated is gone. When I re-open for editing to check the link, it is gone.

After entering a hyperlink in a page and verifying that it works, the link is replaced with "nofollow" in <a href> when I save.
h4. Steps to reproduce

1. Create a page and add a link to a local file.
(i.e. [file:////server/path/file.txt|file:///server/path/file.txt])

2. Save the page and confirm that the link is working. In page source we can see:
{code:java}
<a href="file:////server/path/file.txt" class="external-link" rel="nofollow">file:////server/path/file.txt</a>
{code}
3. Edit the page - don't need to actually edit, just enter in edit mode to trigger the bug and then exit.

4. The link doesn't work anymore. Checking the source code:
{code:java}
<a rel="nofollow">file:////server/path/file.txt</a>
{code}

