Currently there's no option to turn off caching via UI for the "jira" macro.  The workaround is to hack it via [Confluence Source Editor|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.editor.confluence-source-editor], and add the following parameter to the macro:
{code}
<ac:parameter ac:name="cache">off</ac:parameter>
{code}
So that it looks like this:
{code}
 <ac:macro ac:name="jira">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="cache">off</ac:parameter>
    <ac:parameter ac:name="server">Your Company JIRA</ac:parameter>
    <ac:parameter ac:name="jqlQuery">project = test</ac:parameter>
  </ac:macro>
{code}

Turning the cache off in the JIRA macro will prevent un-updated views of JIRA filters (such as when an issue is moved to another project, but the issue is still shown in the old project in the JIRA macro)

