{{Show logo and title}} and {{Site title}} settings at *Confluence Admin > Site Logo* are not stored into the database.

h3. *Steps to reproduce*
# Modify site title and/or setting to show logo and title at *Confluence Admin > Site Logo*
# Check the database by {code:sql}select BANDANAVALUE from BANDANA where BANDANAKEY='atlassian.confluence.settings';{code}
# Notice, the settings in the XML are not stored
# Restart Confluence, notice the settings are gone

h3. *Workaround*
(!) *Be sure to perform the following with great caution!*
# Shut down Confluence
# (!) *Create a backup of your Confluence database!*
# Query the settings from the database using {code:sql}select BANDANAVALUE from BANDANA where BANDANAKEY='atlassian.confluence.settings';{code}
# Modify the following values accordingly in the XML, for the desired setting: 
-- {noformat}  <showApplicationTitle>false</showApplicationTitle>{noformat} 
-- {noformat}  <siteTitle>Confluence</siteTitle>{noformat}
-- To show the application title, set the first value to {{true}} from {{false}}, to change the site title, change {{Confluence}} for the desired value. Be sure to save the whole database value back in the same format as before, pay extra attention to character encoding and line break characters.
# Start Confluence

